name: acetaldehyde dehydrogenase (acetylating)

name: acetate reversible transport via proton symport
2-Oxoglutarate dehydrogenase
equation: [c] : coa + nad + akg --> nadh + co2 + succoa

name: ATP synthase (four protons for one ATP)
equation: adp[c] + (4) h[e] + pi[c] <==> (3) h[c] + atp[c] + h2o[c]
rule: (((b3736 and b3737 and b3738) and (b3731 and b3732 and b3733 and b3734 and b3735)) or ((b3736 and b3737 and b3738) and (b3731 and b3732 and b3733 and b3734 and b3735) and b3739))

name: citrate synthase
equation: [c] : accoa + h2o + oaa --> coa + h + cit

formate transport via proton symport (uptake only)
fumarate reductase

rule: (b1817 and b1818 and b1819 and b2415 and b2416)

name: glutamine synthetase
equation: [c] : atp + glu_L + nh4 --> h + adp + pi + gln_L

equation: atp[c] + h2o[c] + gln_L[e] --> h[c] + adp[c] + pi[c] + gln_L[c]

equation: [c] : h2o + glu_L + nadp <==> h + akg + nadph + nh4

name: glutamate synthase (NADPH)

malate synthase
equation: [c] : accoa + h2o + glx --> coa + h + mal_L

name: pyruvate dehydrogenase
equation: [c] : coa + nad + pyr --> accoa + nadh + co2

phosphoenolpyruvate carboxylase
equation: [c] : h2o + co2 + pep --> h + pi + oaa

name: phosphoenolpyruvate synthase

name: NAD(P) transhydrogenase
equation: nadh[c] + (2) h[e] + nadp[c] --> nad[c] + (2) h[c] + nadph[c]
